job.job_description: Join Intuit in this exciting opportunity.

This is an early-career position where you’ll gain hands-on experience building frontend features, fixing bugs, and learning modern web development practices. You will work with senior engineers and cross-functional partners to deliver customer-first solutions that simplify financial workflows for millions of small businesses.


Responsibilities

  • Implement simple UI features or bug fixes using JavaScript, HTML, and CSS within established architecture.
  • Collaborate with senior engineers, designers, and product managers in an agile development team.
  • Write well-documented, testable code and participate in code reviews.
  • Assist in integrating frontend components with backend APIs and services.
  • Debug and resolve defects with guidance from more experienced engineers.
  • Learn and apply engineering best practices such as test-driven development (TDD), accessibility, and responsive design.
  • Gain exposure to the Fintech domain, including customer experiences related to invoicing, payments, and money movement.

Qualifications

  • Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science or related field, or equivalent practical experience.
  • Academic or personal project experience with frontend technologies (JavaScript, HTML, CSS).
  • Understanding of basic programming concepts, version control, and software testing.
  • Willingness to learn secure software development practices and CI/CD workflows.
  • Strong problem-solving mindset and a collaborative, growth-oriented attitude.
  • Familiarity with any JavaScript SPA framework (e.g., React, Angular, Vue) is a plus.

Intuit provides a competitive compensation package with a strong pay for performance rewards approach. This position will be eligible for a cash bonus, equity rewards and benefits, in accordance with our applicable plans and programs (see more about our compensation and benefits at Intuit®: Careers | Benefits). Pay offered is based on factors such as job-related knowledge, skills, experience, and work location. Position Summary...What you'll do...Senior Data Scientist for Walmart Claim Services 
Location: Bentonville, AR 
Join us in revolutionizing data-driven decision-making in the world’s largest company! Walmart Claim Services (WCS) is looking for a talented Staff Data Scientist to support our team of over 550 professional who operate like an internal insurance company, managing claims for our associates and customers across the nation. 
About Us: 
WCS works closely with our Legal, Safety, & Finance partner and external vendors to provide data insights for informed, data-driven decisions. Our data science and analytics team consist of talented group of data specialists who manage data, develop statistical, machine learning, NLP, Gen AI models/ solutions, and maintain reporting tools, ensuring we remain a world-class business. 
As a Staff Data Scientist, you will utilize your expertise in data mining, predictive modeling, machine learning, and NLP techniques to drive strategic decisions for WCS. You will be at the forefront of implementing models and strategies using A/B testing or Design of Experiments (DOE), tracking business performance, and providing insightful visualizations to support and continuously improve WCS business strategy. 
Key Responsibilities: Design, develop and Deploy innovative Machine Learning, Natural Language Processing (NLP), AI Agents, Gen AI, and Graph Neural Network (GNN) models using Python/GCP or other modeling tools.Design and conduct A/B Testing and multivariate experiments (DOE), tracking results to provide actionable recommendations to business partners.Develop clear, concise, and powerful data visualizations using BI tools like Power BI or Tableau.Utilize SQL, Python, Google Cloud, MLOps, Tableau, Power BI, R or SAS to prepare data for analysis, modeling, deployment, and reporting.Identify business process gaps and devise analytical solutions to address them.
Ideal Candidate: A self-starter, able to work independently and overcome obstacles to achieve results.A multi-tasker, capable of managing multiple technical projects while delivering results.A problem solver, with a high degree of intellectual curiosity and solid business acumen.An excellent communicator, able to present significant analysis in a concise manner to key stakeholders.A flexible thinker, comfortable with ambiguity and adept at fact-finding.
 
In joining Walmart’s WCS team, you get to be part of a global company that is at the forefront of leveraging data for business insights. This role offers the opportunity to work with complex, large-scale datasets, and cutting-edge technologies, providing a platform for continuous learning and professional growth. Furthermore, Walmart’s commitment to innovation makes it an exciting environment for data analysts who want to make a significant impact. 
 
 At Walmart, we offer competitive pay as well as performance-based bonus awards and other great benefits for a happier mind, body, and wallet. Health benefits include medical, vision and dental coverage. Financial benefits include 401(k), stock purchase and company-paid life insurance. Paid time off benefits include PTO (including sick leave), parental leave, family care leave, bereavement, jury duty, and voting. You will also receive PTO and/or PPTO that can be used for vacation, sick leave, holidays, or other purposes. The amount you receive depends on your job classification and length of employment. It will meet or exceed the requirements of paid sick leave laws, where applicable. 
 
For information about PTO, see https://one.walmart.com/notices.

Programs range from high school completion to bachelor's degrees, including English Language Learning and short-form certificates. Tuition, books, and fees are completely paid for by Walmart.

Looking for an opportunity to make an impact?  At Leidos, we deliver innovative solutions through the efforts of our diverse and talented people who are dedicated to our customers’ success. We empower our teams, contribute to our communities, and operate sustainable. Everything we do is built on a commitment to do the right thing for our customers, our people, and our community. Our Mission, Vision, and Values guide the way we do business.  Your greatest work is ahead!  Leidos’ Defense Systems, Sensor Systems Analysis & Engineering Portfolio, is seeking a talented entry-level software developer with the ability and experience to work multiple projects (primarily modeling & simulation efforts but also opportunities to work with hardware integration) within the Sensor Systems Analysis and Engineering Portfolio.   You will join a diverse team of junior-to-senior software developers, engineers, and scientists to help create unique solutions for complex problems. Our team solves important problems that make a difference and support our customers in the current and future defense of our nation; primarily in the areas of modeling & simulation, sensor integration, testing, characterization, modeling, simulation, data analysis, and algorithm development for electro-optical infrared (EO/IR) systems. The ideal developer candidate will also demonstrate experience in and/or enthusiasm toward developing a broader technical capability to support overlapping engineering and scientific disciplines with a particular focus on writing software to solve problems. Candidate will be expected to support multiple tasks in parallel, productively contribute to a team environment, and communicate effectively to management, coworkers, and customers.  You’ll work within an established and very skilled team, alongside other contractors and our customers.  Joining our team offers the opportunity to work with experts in their field and grow your career in an area that is appealing to you. You will quickly become an integral member of our team and be given the opportunity to take responsibility for challenging problems of your own. Because of this, we seek team members that are driven and engaged in their work while simultaneously demonstrating high character, given that you will often be working on sensitive and unique problems which require a high degree of trust from our customers.   If this sounds like the kind of environment where you can thrive, keep reading!   Leidos Defense Systems Sector provides a diverse portfolio of systems, solutions, and services covering land, sea, air, space, and cyberspace for customers worldwide. Solutions for Defense include enterprise and mission IT, large-scale intelligence systems, command and control, geospatial and data analytics, cybersecurity, logistics, training, and intelligence analysis and operations support. Our team is solving the world’s toughest security challenges for customers with “can’t fail” missions. To explore and learn more, click here!  Are you ready to make an impact? Share your resume with us today!  ​​Primary Responsibilities. ​ ​Candidate can expect to work closely with a team of engineers and scientists to write software (using primarily C++ and Python) to solve problems in a variety of disciplines to include EO/IR sensor systems, primarily for modeling & simulation purposes. ​Candidate is also expected to have the ability to work and to communicate effectively within a multidisciplinary team and have familiarity with software development for both Windows and Linux OS. ​ ​Basic Qualifications.   ​​Candidate must possess at least a bachelor’s degree from an accredited university in software engineering, computer science, or an equivalent engineering or science degree and ​0+ years of experience in a related field. ​Experience with C++/Python and version control systems such as Git. ​Must be a U.S. citizen and able to obtain and maintain a DoW security clearance. ​Candidate must be a resident of the North Alabama area or willing to relocate to the Huntsville – North Alabama, AL, area. ​ ​Preferred Qualifications.  ​​In addition to the qualifications listed above, the ideal candidate should be highly organized, demonstrating the ability to work independently at times due to a fast-paced and highly productive work environment. Because the candidate may fill various project needs, an interest in working multiple programs with intermediate ability in C++, C#, and Python is a bonus along with strong object-oriented design skills, the ability to create design documentation, requirements specifications, and other technical documentation.  ​Preference may be given to candidates with one or more of the following: recent stellar academic performance, a SECRET clearance or above; a TS/SCI clearance (with CI Polygraph); familiarity or interest in EO/IR phenomenology; experience with image processing; experience with GPU programming and/or CUDA programming; experience with developing AI/ML solutions; experience with build systems such as CMake.​ Come break things (in a good way). Then build them smarter.We're the tech company everyone calls when things get weird. We don’t wear capes (they’re a safety hazard), but we do solve high-stakes problems with code, caffeine, and a healthy disregard for “how it’s always been done.”Original Posting:December 17, 2025For U.S. Positions: While subject to change based on business needs, Leidos reasonably anticipates that this job requisition will remain open for at least 3 days with an anticipated close date of no earlier than 3 days after the original posting date as listed above.Pay Range:Pay Range $57,850.00 - $104,575.00The Leidos pay range for this job level is a general guideline only and not a guarantee of compensation or salary.
